KnowledgeBase.Title: Example Void compareGE 008
KnowledgeBase.RelatedFunctions: compare compareEQ compareNE compareGT compareLT compareLE

Example.Description: These examples use the compareGE function to compare two objects and return the Boolean value, true or false. The values of each object are compared to determine whether the first object is greater or equal in value than the second object.

Syntax.Note: The uninitialized value of x is equal to #void.
The value #void is not greater or equal than the value of the String.
